dium.  The Cleric armor that is so heavy is still lighter than medium plate, so the Erudites and Humans already had a little relief.<P>I would hope that Dark Elves would have some quests that they could do at all though.  Verant has taken a giant leap forward with Clerics if they continue adding items to the different races.  Give Dwarves something for their Battle Cleric lifestyle (hehe).  Give High Elves something appropriate to their more serene outlook.  Give Gnomes a way of using their Tinkering perhaps.  A weapon that procs at 24 and summons a level 14 tinkered pet with a time limit that only procs when used against something that gives experience?  Base it upon their Tinkering skill (yeah, very expensive to raise high) to give a better pet each level.<P>What type of items do you think appropriate for your race of Cleric?  So far, Humans and Erudites have : <BR>1) Light weight stuff that has great AC (without losing much Wisdom if any for the item), <BR>2) added Magic Resistance, and <BR>3) a couple of neat effects.  Hopefully, such items will be added to give all the Races their own defining attributes.<P>Me?  I was happy just getting a veil that would have better AC than a Platinum Ruby veil and an Effect.  Now we learn that we need fear the dark no longer.  It has been tough fighting undead at night when you can't see well.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Throckjr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I tell you what...  It wasn't worth doing the shining star of light quest.  I got so much value out of it that I went and hunted treants to get to level 27!  I can't begin to tell you how many gnolls I killed just to get into Qeynos to turn in bone chips til that stupid pally gave me the quest, only to find out that I needed to be higher to get the SSL!!!  This is after running it twice to find out it was timed AND had to NOT be done at night!!  All this before I knew that Allakazham's exi